\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
First, during the design of the endline questionnaire, we tried to minimize
 experimenter demand effects by careful formulation of the questions.
 Experimenter demand effects are more likely in simple yes/no questions
 than for more open ended questions.
 For instance, in our endline survey, we did not ask if the farmers used
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

plant spacing of 75cm x 30cm with a reduced seed rate of 1 seed per hill
\begin_inset Quotes erd
